  "market_context": "Gold was in a corrective phase after an impulse move down; equal lows formed near 1796.000, with buy-side liquidity at 1815.000 and sell-side liquidity at 1796.000 on the 1H chart.",
  "key_observation": "A bearish candle closed below equal lows (1796.000), triggering a liquidity sweep of sell-side stops, then price immediately reversed back into the range—confirming a valid liquidity sweep pattern.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a fair value gap (FVG) between ~1803.000 and 1808.000 indicating buyside imbalance and sellside inefficiency.",
    "Step 2: Observed a bearish candle closing below equal lows at 1796.000, followed by immediate re-entry into the range—confirming a liquidity sweep of sell-side liquidity.",
    "Step 3: Based on market maker model, anticipated price movement toward buy-side liquidity at 1815.000 after the sweep.",
    "Step 4: Zoomed into 15-minute chart to locate entry; required a change of character (break and close above a key level) to confirm short-term reversal.",
    "Step 5: Defined trade setup: wait for price to return to the FVG zone (~1803–1808), enter long, place stop loss below the FVG area."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Liquidity sweeps at equal lows often precede reversals toward opposing liquidity; confirmation via change of character and FVG retest improves trade reliability and risk-reward.",
